        {
            "review_id": "226827176",
            "steam_id": "76561198881334304",
            "playtime_minutes": 17966,
            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 0,
            "weighted_score": 0.5,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "The only medieval strategy game where you can both command armies in the field in real time and play on a campaign map. Less historically accurate than other TW titles but there was still a good amount of research that went into the game for an early 2000s game.\r\n\r\nI wish they wouldn't go with the gloomy medieval aesthetic over a more realistic colorful one. \r\nIt's also a shame that you can't do grandcampaign + field battle simulteneously online. Hope they fix the latter issue in Medieval III. \r\nIt would have also been nice to see the campaign mechanics reflect feudal politics like Cruisader Kings."
        },
