        {
            "review_id": "225812727",
            "steam_id": "76561199055435675",
            "playtime_minutes": 42731,
            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 0,
            "weighted_score": 0.5,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "MW2 & Shogun 2 are my favorite TW chapters. 1600 hours between them. The family structure is compelling- and MW2 somehow has the best individualization of any of the TW catalogue. Each descriptor adds flavor, personality, and benefits to governance and generalship, as well as attractiveness for princesses- who function as roving diplomats, spies, and marriage pieces. I've moved a new princess across the entirety of the map to marry and specific general who had the right stats, name (Roy), or political value in the bloodline. It's the best. Battles are inevitably who has the most armored horses, and economy is just who has most farms, and endgame isn't as epic as Realm divide or WH2 massive onslaughts. But the story is the bloodline and marriage and bloodfeuds with other princes/ kings in the early - middle stages of game. I love it. Will play forever. I hear the songs in my dreams sometimes. 10/10"
        },
